TY  - JOUR
TI  - Misperceived Social Norms
AU  - Bursztyn, Leonardo
AU  - González, Alessandra L.
AU  - Yanagizawa-Drott, David
AB  - [We show that the vast majority of young married men in Saudi Arabia privately support women working outside the home (WWOH) and substantially underestimate support by other similar men. Correcting these beliefs increases men’s (costly) willingness to help their wives search for jobs. Months later, wives of men whose beliefs were corrected are more likely to have applied and interviewed for a job outside the home. In a recruitment experiment with a local company, randomly informing women about actual support for WWOH leads them to switch from an at-home temporary enumerator job to a higher-paying, outside-the-home version of the job.]
